cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.IT, cs.CG, cs.LG 

Reasoning: 

- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science): Homotopy type theory is a branch of mathematics that merges insights from abstract homotopy theory and higher category theory with those of logic and type theory. This paper presents a proof in homotopy type theory, which is a logical system, so it is likely to belong to this category. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages): Homotopy type theory has connections to programming languages, as it provides a foundation for constructive mathematics and can be used to develop new programming languages. This paper may be of interest to researchers in this area. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory): Homotopy type theory has connections to information theory, as it provides a framework for understanding the structure of mathematical objects and their relationships. This paper may be relevant to researchers interested in the information-theoretic aspects of homotopy type theory. 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry): The torus and the product of two circles are geometric objects, and homotopy type theory provides a way to represent them as type-theoretic constructions. This paper may be of interest to researchers in computational geometry who are interested in the representation of geometric objects in type theory. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): This category is less likely, but homotopy type theory has connections to machine learning through its use in developing new foundations for mathematics and computer science.
